definitions.definition: A fixed telephone communications cable ; originally, one run over land, as opposed to a submarine cable.
A telephone connected by such a fixed wire that allows multiple phones to operate simultaneously on the same phone number, specifically not wireless / mobile .
That which is connected by such a fixed wire (telephone, internet etc.).

main_definition: A fixed telephone communications cable ; originally, one run over land, as opposed to a submarine cable.
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) A telephone connected by such a fixed wire that allows multiple phones to operate simultaneously on the same phone number, specifically not wireless / mobile .
( attributively ) That which is connected by such a fixed wire (telephone, internet etc.).
